Looking at how the client uses it:

```typescript
// DescriptionSection.tsx:72
onClick={() => onEntityClick(formatSourceRef(entry.source!))}
// where formatSourceRef returns `${ref.tb}:${ref.id}` → "message:abc123"
```

The end goal is just the string `"message:abc123"` passed to `onEntityClick`. So the client doesn't need the object — a plain string is enough.

The simpler fix is on the client: treat `source` as a `string` instead of `{ tb, id }`.

